FL,353,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F352A1774887078
OL,3,CFarmers oppose plans to re-introduce
OL,4,Csea eagles
OL,6,FThe Cumbrian White-Tailed Eagle
OL,7,FProject, led by The Lifescape Project
OL,8,Fcharity, wants to see these birds re-
OL,9,Fintroduced to Cumbria, but local
OL,10,Ffarmers have expressed their
OL,11,Fopposition to the plans.
OL,13,FWill Cockbain, a sheep farmer, said:
OL,14,F"Sea eagles have the potential to
OL,15,Fcause serious sheep predation, we've
OL,16,Fseen it in the west coast of Scotland
OL,17,Fwhere losses can be quite high.
OL,19,F"The Lake District is not the place
OL,20,Ffor sea eagles.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,353,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F352A1774887078
OL,3,CFarmers oppose plans to re-introduce
OL,4,Csea eagles
OL,6,F"What about the sea eagles themselves?
OL,7,FThey're planning on releasing 66
OL,8,F(eagles) - that's quite a high number,
OL,9,Fas Lifescape, the organisation behind
OL,10,Fit, themselves know that there will be
OL,11,Fa high mortality (rate of sea eagles)."
OL,13,FRichard Pedley, Cumbria County Chair
OL,14,Fof the National Farmer's Union, said:
OL,15,F"White tailed eagles not only take
OL,16,Ffish, they've been proven to take
OL,17,Flambs, wildlife, birds, black
OL,18,Fgrouse... they can cause devastation.
OL,20,F"We need to be really careful about
OL,21,Fhow we handle this."
OL,26,@pD@ApmpD@HpnsD@RpmsD@epn
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/6
